[[File:Bubenečská čistírna (03).jpg|thumb|Entrance of the building]]
'''Sewage Plant in Bubeneč''' is the oldest [[sewage treatment plant]] in [[Prague]] designed by [[William Heerlein Lindley]] and built between 1895-1906. In 1991 whole building was declared a protected national monument and has been converted into the Eco-technical Museum.<ref>{{Citation | title = Museum commemorates 100 years of Prague Sewer |first= Michael  |last= Longaro |url= http://www.radio.cz/de/artikel/80660 |work= Český rozhlas ([[Czech Radio]]) |date= June 30, 2006 |accessdate= February 23, 2010}}</ref>

